  "transcript": [
    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 1.44,
      "end": 3.04,
      "text": "This is a Libra box recording.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 4.0,
      "end": 5.96,
      "text": "All Libra box recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 6.74,
      "end": 13.0,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit librarybox.org, recorded by Hainau-Opgenhein.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 14.1,
      "end": 15.06,
      "text": "Asop's Fables.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 16.76,
      "end": 18.58,
      "text": "The Apes and the Two Travelers.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 19.6,
      "end": 26.34,
      "text": "Two men were travelling together, one of whom never spoke to truth, whereas the other never",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 26.34,
      "end": 27.04,
      "text": "told a lie.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 28.04,
      "end": 31.2,
      "text": "And they came in the course of the travels to the land of Apes.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 31.72,
      "end": 37.06,
      "text": "The king of the Apes, hearing of their arrival, ordered them to be brought before him.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 37.84,
      "end": 43.0,
      "text": "And by way of impressing them with his magnificence, he received them sitting on a throne.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 44.04,
      "end": 48.94,
      "text": "While the Apes, his subjects, were arranged in long rows on either side of him.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 49.88,
      "end": 55.48,
      "text": "When the Travelers came into his presence, he asked them what they thought of him as a",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 55.48,
      "end": 55.68,
      "text": "king.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 55.68,
      "end": 63.56,
      "text": "The lying Traveler said, Sir, everyone must see that you are the most noble and mighty",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 63.56,
      "end": 63.96,
      "text": "monarch.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-015",
      "start": 64.88,
      "end": 66.84,
      "text": "And what do you think of my subjects?",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-016",
      "start": 67.62,
      "end": 68.54,
      "text": "Continued the king?",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-017",
      "start": 69.3,
      "end": 74.06,
      "text": "They, said the Traveler, are in every way worthy of their Royal Master.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-018",
      "start": 75.5,
      "end": 80.8,
      "text": "The Apes were so delighted with his answer that he gave him a very handsome present.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-019",
      "start": 81.54,
      "end": 87.4,
      "text": "The other Traveler thought that if his companion was rewarded so splendidly for telling a lie,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-020",
      "start": 88.28,
      "end": 92.94,
      "text": "he himself would certainly receive a still greater reward for telling the truth.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-021",
      "start": 93.8,
      "end": 99.9,
      "text": "So, when the Ape turned to him and said, and what, Sir, is your opinion?",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-022",
      "start": 101.02,
      "end": 108.36,
      "text": "He replied, I think you are a very fine ape, and all your subjects are fine Apes too.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-023",
      "start": 109.34,
      "end": 115.7,
      "text": "The king of the Apes was so enraged at his reply that he ordered him to be taken away",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-024",
      "start": 115.7,
      "end": 117.52,
      "text": "and clawed to death.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-025",
      "start": 119.24,
      "end": 122.52,
      "text": "End of the Apes and the two Travelers.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
